    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PMCH subframe detection in FDD 4-frames mode\n\n### Summary\nThe `is_pmch_subframe()` function in `pmch_common.c` was not correctly identifying PMCH subframes when operating in FDD 4-frames mode. This caused the eNB to incorrectly schedule PMCH transmissions, leading to missed multicast data delivery.\n\nThe issue was in the bit manipulation logic for extracting subframe configuration from the 4-frames bitmap. The function was applying shifted bitmasks to the configuration value instead of shifting the configuration value itself.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/pmch_common.c`: \n  - Fixed bit manipulation in FDD 4-frames case by shifting `mbsfn_SubframeConfig` right by `j*6` bits before applying masks\n  - Corrected logic in `is_fembms_pmch_subframe()` to properly return PMCH status\n  - Added clarifying comments to explain function behavior\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure eNB with MBSFN configuration using 4-frames pattern\n2. Set FDD mode\n3. Monitor PMCH scheduling - some subframes that should be PMCH are not being scheduled\n4. Observe that multicast traffic is not delivered consistently across all configured subframes\n\nThe fix ensures that when the 4-frames flag is set, the correct bits are extracted from the subframe allocation bitmap for each of the four consecutive frames.\n"
}